President Buhari arrives in Katsina for governorship election V/O: President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived in Katsina for Saturday’s gubernatorial elections after a resounding re-election victory. This is the president’s first visit to his home state after his re-election. Expectedly, the Nigerian leader received a hero’s welcome as he arrived at the Umaru Yar’Adua Airport at 6:05 p.m and was received by the State Governor, Aminu Bello Masari. The president then departed Katsina in a chopper for Daura where he will exercise his franchise. 